data.name: Wee Whistle Stop Cafe
data.full_address: Wee Whistle Stop Cafe, Loch Torridon Community Centre, Torridon, Achnasheen IV22 2EZ, United Kingdom

reviews.review_text: What a gem to find on our journey through the Highlands! It’s right by the water, so you’ll overlook the lake as you sip your morning tea or coffee. We saw a beautiful rainbow while having our breakfast! I ordered the Scottish breakfast and it was my first time eating black pudding. I really enjoyed the whole meal and it was enough to share with my friend. The employees were so kind and helpful when making suggestions for stops on our journey. What a lovely find - made our trip even better.

reviews.review_text:
A lovely wee cafe located in a particularly beautiful nature reserve, small snacks and also full meals available with very tasty coffees and cakes also.

Fairly expensive but very much worth the price as everything is fresh and cooked to order.

Staff were friendly. The cashier noticed she made a mistake on the bill and rectified this when we didn't even notice ourselves. Would highly recommend to anyone passing who needs some more fuel for the road

reviews.review_text: Fantastic food, beautiful ingredients well prepared. Huge selection of dishes including an extensive specials board. Staff were friendly and professional. Vegan and vegetarian options. The ginger and pear cake is so delicious.

reviews.review_text: Lovely cafe tucked in the small village in Torridon, about 5 minutes off the NC500 route. They serve wonderful baked items and coffee/tea which were all value for money. Overall vibe was splendid with a million dollar view of the Loch. Support local businesses when visiting the NC500!

Overall vibe was splendid with a million dollar view of the Loch. Support local businesses when visiting the NC500!

reviews.review_text: Open early (8am)! I had a lovely smoked salmon and fresh scrambled eggs with a flat white coffee with oatmilk. Locally run - a great spot to have breakfast in one of the most beautiful places in the world

reviews.review_text: We went for Fish Friday and also had lunch here one day. There was a lively atmosphere on the Friday it was filled with a mix of locals and visitors with a warm and welcoming atmosphere. There was a good range of options on the menu with locall produce ie hot smoked salmon from Sheildaig and prawns.  The food was good couldn't fault it. It is a great community building too a must to visit.

review_services.Recommended dishes: Hot Smoked Trout Poached Egg Avocado and Toast

reviews.review_text: A very nice place to stop for the food and the spectacular views. There is an excellent choice of food and home cooked delights. The staff are all there to make your visit an enjoyable one, especially during these strange times.
reviews.business_response_text:
Thanks so much for your review in 2020 – this will help us to create and improve our 2022 offering. Our 2022 season is looking like a busy one and we hope to see you again. Wishing you happy travels wherever you go.
Lis & the team

reviews.review_text: The most gorgeous setting overlooking the loch where the mountains drop right down to the sea. Very bright and airy place with friendly attentive staff. Only popped in for a cuppa but cakes and menu looked delicious.

reviews.review_text: The only place open a Monday in the Torridon area. The waitress was very kind and helpful. The food was well prepared and delicious! We loved the Salmon especially, as well as the bacon.

reviews.review_text:
How hard is it to make a Toastie I sometimes wonder. Some places seem to really struggle, but not here! They were able to present me the perfect Toastie. Crisp, but not burned. Cheesy, and all molten. Squished, but not flat. And they even added a tasty homemade chutney. All the variables were right!

Also the view is great and the staff are very warm and welcoming. But don't trust me, go try for yourself!

reviews.review_text:
Best venison burger we had in Scotland!
This cafe is a perfect roadside stop, especially if you're hungry. Outdoor seating overlooking the loch, local beers were yum, great coffee, amazing looking cakes - for a small place you can't ask for anything better. The staff do a super job!
reviews.business_response_text:
Thank you so much for your five-star review. The team are delighted to hear that you had a positive experience with us at the Wee Whistle Stop. We hope you’ll visit us again, tell your friends about us and enjoy your travels wherever you go.
Best Wishes
Lis & the team
